## Goal

Implement the safety guardrail that REQUIRES users to type a specific phrase to proceed with unencrypted exports.

## Why This Matters

- GitHub Pages sites are **always publicly accessible**
- Unencrypted exports expose all conversation content to anyone
- This should be strongly discouraged but possible for advanced users
- A checkbox isn't enough - require explicit acknowledgment

## Implementation

### CLI Flow

```rust
pub fn confirm_unencrypted_export() -> Result<bool, ExportError> {
    if !config.encryption_enabled {
        eprintln!("{}", style("⚠️  SECURITY WARNING").red().bold());
        eprintln!();
        eprintln!("You are about to export WITHOUT ENCRYPTION.");
        eprintln!();
        eprintln!("This means:");
        eprintln!("  • All conversation content will be publicly readable");
        eprintln!("  • Anyone with the URL can view your data");
        eprintln!("  • Search engines may index your content");
        eprintln!("  • There is NO way to restrict access later");
        eprintln!();
        eprintln!("{}", style("This is IRREVERSIBLE once deployed.").yellow());
        eprintln!();
        eprintln!("To proceed, type exactly:");
        eprintln!();
        eprintln!("  {}", style("I UNDERSTAND AND ACCEPT THE RISKS").cyan());
        eprintln!();
        eprint!("Your input: ");
        std::io::stdout().flush()?;

        let mut input = String::new();
        std::io::stdin().read_line(&mut input)?;

        if input.trim() != "I UNDERSTAND AND ACCEPT THE RISKS" {
            eprintln!();
            eprintln!("{}", style("Export cancelled.").green());
            eprintln!("To export with encryption (recommended), remove --no-encryption");
            return Err(ExportError::UnencryptedNotConfirmed);
        }

        // Additional confirmation
        eprintln!();
        eprintln!("Are you ABSOLUTELY SURE? [y/N]: ");
        let mut confirm = String::new();
        std::io::stdin().read_line(&mut confirm)?;

        if confirm.trim().to_lowercase() != "y" {
            return Err(ExportError::UnencryptedNotConfirmed);
        }
    }

    Ok(true)
}
```

### JSON/Robot Mode

In JSON mode, unencrypted export is BLOCKED by default:

```bash
