### New Module: src/pages/deploy_github.rs

### Deployment Flow

1. Check Prerequisites
   - gh CLI installed
   - gh auth status passes
   - Network connectivity

2. Create Repository (if needed)
   gh repo create <name> --public --description "..."

3. Clone to Temp Directory
   git clone <repo-url> temp-dir

4. Copy Bundle Contents
   - Clear existing files
   - Copy site/ directory contents
   - Create .nojekyll file
   - Add robots.txt

5. Commit and Push (Orphan Branch)
   git checkout --orphan gh-pages
   git add -A
   git commit -m "Deploy cass archive"
   git push -f origin gh-pages

6. Enable GitHub Pages
   gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/pages -X POST \
      -f source.branch=gh-pages -f source.path=/

7. Return URL
   https://<owner>.github.io/<repo>

### Prerequisites Struct

struct Prerequisites {
    gh_cli: Option<String>,        // Version if installed
    gh_authenticated: bool,
    disk_space_mb: u64,
    estimated_size_mb: u64,
}

